WEBVTT

00:01.668 --> 00:03.420
[melodic whistling]

00:03.503 --> 00:04.921
[smacking]

00:05.004 --> 00:05.880
[exhaling deeply]

00:05.964 --> 00:07.465
thump!
both: WHOA!

00:07.549 --> 00:09.342
- ♪ HERE WE GO 'CAUSE WE'RE
FANBOY AND CHUM CHUM ♪

00:09.426 --> 00:10.969
♪ A LITTLE CUCKOO,
FANBOY AND CHUM CHUM ♪

00:11.052 --> 00:13.388
♪ WE'RE AMAZING,
TOTALLY CRAZY ♪

00:13.471 --> 00:14.431
♪ FANBOY AND CHUM CHUM ♪

00:14.514 --> 00:15.974
♪ COME ON, EVERYBODY, SING ♪

00:16.056 --> 00:17.475
♪ WE'RE GONNA SCREAM
AT THE TOP OF OUR LUNGS ♪

00:17.559 --> 00:18.476
♪ WE'RE GONNA FLY
AND HAVE SOME FUN ♪

00:18.560 --> 00:20.937
♪ WE DON'T CARE IF YOU STARE ♪

00:21.020 --> 00:22.981
♪ OR EVEN
LOOK AT OUR UNDERWEAR ♪

00:23.064 --> 00:24.524
both: ♪ BRAIN ♪

00:24.607 --> 00:26.526
♪ FREEZE ♪

00:26.609 --> 00:27.902
♪ OOH ♪

00:27.986 --> 00:29.279
♪ BRAIN FREEZE! ♪

00:29.362 --> 00:30.864
- ♪ BUH-BUH, BAH,
BAH, BAH, BAH, BAH, BAH ♪

00:30.947 --> 00:32.949
♪ BUH-BUH, BAH, BAH-BAH,
BUH, BAH-BAH, BAH ♪

00:33.032 --> 00:34.492
♪ BAH, BAH, BAH, BAH ♪

00:34.576 --> 00:36.244
♪ BUH-BUH, BAH-BAH,
BUH-BAH, BAH ♪

00:36.327 --> 00:37.370
♪ COME AND SCREAM
AT THE TOP OF YOUR LUNGS ♪

00:37.454 --> 00:39.330
♪ COME AND FLY
AND HAVE SOME FUN ♪

00:39.414 --> 00:40.331
♪ BUH-BUH, BAH ♪

00:40.415 --> 00:41.750
♪ BUH-BUH, BAH ♪

00:41.833 --> 00:43.251
♪ BUH-BUH, BAH, BAH,
FANBOY AND CHUM CHUM ♪

00:43.334 --> 00:44.210
both: OH!
- THAT'S NICE.

00:55.638 --> 00:58.308
[whirring]

00:58.391 --> 01:00.310
- AND NOW THE MOMENT
YOU'VE ALL BEEN WAITING FOR:

01:00.393 --> 01:03.980
THE FROSTY MART
DREAM VACATION GIVEAWAY...

01:04.063 --> 01:07.108
[echoing]
GIVEAWAY...GIVEAWAY...

01:07.192 --> 01:09.652
FUNNY. I EXPECTED
A BIGGER TURNOUT,

01:09.736 --> 01:11.738
ESPECIALLY CONSIDERING THE
THOUSANDS OF PROMOTIONAL FLIERS

01:11.821 --> 01:12.906
I HAD YOU PASS OUT.

01:12.989 --> 01:15.825
- [chuckling sheepishly]
YEAH, FUNNY.

01:15.909 --> 01:17.410
[lid creaks open]

01:17.494 --> 01:19.496
OOPSIE.

01:19.579 --> 01:20.914
- OH, WELL.
HERE WE GO.

01:20.997 --> 01:25.001
[grunting]
UH...NO, IN HERE...AH.

01:25.084 --> 01:25.668
AND THE WINNER IS...

01:25.752 --> 01:28.838
- COME ON, JUST SAY IT:

01:28.922 --> 01:32.008
LENNY FLYNN-BOYLE.

01:32.091 --> 01:34.844
- FANBOY AND CHUM CHUM.

01:34.928 --> 01:36.095
- HUH?

01:36.179 --> 01:37.847
- YES?

01:37.931 --> 01:38.932
- YOU WON!

01:39.015 --> 01:39.849
- HUH?

01:39.933 --> 01:41.100
- [angrily] WHAT?

01:41.184 --> 01:45.230
both: WE WON! WE WON!
WE WON, WE WON, WE WON!

01:45.313 --> 01:46.689
- WAIT A MINUTE.
WHAT DID WE WIN?

01:46.773 --> 01:52.111
- WHY, YOU'VE JUST WON
A FROSTY MART DREAM VACATION.

01:52.195 --> 01:54.239
both: ♪ FROSTY MART DREAM
VACATION! ♪

01:54.322 --> 01:56.866
♪ FROSTY MART DREAM VACATION!
FROSTY MART DREAM VACATION! ♪

01:56.950 --> 01:58.785
♪ FROSTY MART DREAM VACATION! ♪

01:58.868 --> 02:00.870
- BUT THAT'S IMPOSSIBLE.

02:00.954 --> 02:04.207
I STUFFED THE BALLOT BOX MYSELF.

02:04.290 --> 02:06.334
THIS ISN'T EVEN AN ENTRY FORM.

02:06.417 --> 02:07.710
IT'S A SPELLING TEST...

02:07.794 --> 02:10.505
THAT YOU FAILED!

02:10.588 --> 02:12.257
- YEP, BUT WE SPELLED
OUR NAMES RIGHT.

02:12.340 --> 02:13.716
- AND THAT'S ALL THAT MATTERS.

02:13.800 --> 02:16.052
- COME ON, CHUM CHUM,
LET'S GO PACK.

02:16.135 --> 02:16.928
[both laughing gleefully]

02:17.011 --> 02:19.722
- LENNY, HERE ARE THE TICKETS.

02:19.806 --> 02:22.225
A TAXI WILL BE HERE SHORTLY
TO PICK THEM UP.

02:22.308 --> 02:23.226
ONCE THEY'RE SAFELY
ON THEIR WAY,

02:23.309 --> 02:26.563
YOU AND I
WILL HAVE A LITTLE CHAT

02:26.646 --> 02:28.982
ABOUT STUFFING BALLOT BOXES.

02:29.065 --> 02:29.607
JOHNSON OUT.

02:29.691 --> 02:30.608
[fiery blast]

02:30.692 --> 02:33.444
[loud crash]

02:33.528 --> 02:35.238
- [coughing]

02:35.321 --> 02:36.573
THIS ISN'T FAIR.

02:36.656 --> 02:39.450
I DESERVE TO BE
GOING ON THAT VACATION.

02:39.534 --> 02:40.577
[door rings]

02:40.660 --> 02:42.412
both: WE'RE HERE.

02:42.495 --> 02:43.371
- OKAY, RELAX.

02:43.454 --> 02:45.123
THE TAXI ISN'T EVEN HERE YET.

02:45.206 --> 02:46.207
- WHAT DO WE NEED A TAXI FOR?

02:46.291 --> 02:47.292
WE'RE ALREADY HERE.

02:47.375 --> 02:48.710
- HUH?

02:48.793 --> 02:51.379
- OH, SIR, WOULD YOU PLEASE
BRING OUR BAGS TO OUR ROOM?

02:51.462 --> 02:53.131
- WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

02:53.214 --> 02:55.884
- [quietly] LOOKS LIKE THE
LOCALS DON'T SPEAK ENGLISH.

02:55.967 --> 02:57.677
I GOT THIS.

02:57.760 --> 03:02.056
[slowly] PLEASE BRING
OUR BAGS TO OUR ROOM.

03:02.140 --> 03:05.602
- [slowly]
THIS ISN'T A HOTEL.

03:05.685 --> 03:09.480
- UH, HELLO? WE WON
A FROSTY MART DREAM VACATION.

03:09.564 --> 03:13.985
- AND THAT'S WHERE WE ARE,
THE FROSTY MART,

03:14.068 --> 03:17.155
OUR DREAM VACATION.

03:17.238 --> 03:18.448
[door rings]

03:18.531 --> 03:19.991
- WHA?

03:20.074 --> 03:21.743
- LOOK, YOU CAN'T STAY--

03:21.826 --> 03:22.744
- WAIT A MINUTE.

03:22.827 --> 03:24.454
IF THEY STAY HERE,

03:24.537 --> 03:29.459
THEN WE CAN TAKE THOSE TICKETS
AND GO ON A REAL VACATION.

03:29.542 --> 03:30.460
[chuckles]

03:30.543 --> 03:30.960
- I LIKE THE WAY YOU THINK.

03:31.044 --> 03:34.672
[car horn beeps]

03:34.756 --> 03:36.633
- SOMEBODY CALL FOR A TAXI?

03:36.716 --> 03:38.635
- HMM, SPEAK OF THE DEVIL.

03:38.718 --> 03:39.177
- AS A MATTER OF FACT, I BELI--

03:39.260 --> 03:39.761
- OH, LENNY...

03:39.844 --> 03:41.846
[record scratch]

03:41.930 --> 03:43.932
IT'S SUCH A BEAUTIFUL DAY
INSIDE.

03:44.015 --> 03:47.268
COULD YOU BE A PEACH
AND SERVE THESE TO US POOLSIDE?

03:47.352 --> 03:49.938
- WHAT?
WE DON'T HAVE A POOL.

03:50.021 --> 03:53.858
- OH, WELL, GOOD THING
WE BROUGHT OUR TRAVEL POOL.

03:53.942 --> 03:54.901
thump!

03:54.984 --> 03:56.444
- [grunting]

03:56.527 --> 03:59.280
- OH, KEEP ME WAITING, WILL YA?

04:01.324 --> 04:03.409
- CANNONBALL!

04:03.493 --> 04:04.327
[splash]

04:04.410 --> 04:06.663
- I NEED TO GET OUT OF HERE!

04:06.746 --> 04:10.541
- AW, BUT WE WANTED YOU
TO TAKE US SIGHTSEEING.

04:10.625 --> 04:14.504
- [angrily]
SIGHTSEEING? <i> SIGHTSEEING?</i>

04:14.587 --> 04:17.382
OKAY, YEAH,
I'LL TAKE YOU SIGHTSEEING.

04:17.464 --> 04:23.012
I HAVE SOMEPLACE VERY SPECIAL
TO SHOW YOU.

04:23.096 --> 04:24.347
- THIS IS JUST THE STOREROOM.

04:24.430 --> 04:27.350
- OH, IT'S MORE
THAN JUST A STOREROOM.

04:27.433 --> 04:30.436
- YEAH, IT'S THE PLACE
YOU GO TO CRY SOMETIMES.

04:30.520 --> 04:31.688
SO WHAT?

04:31.771 --> 04:35.358
- DID YOU BOYS EVER HEAR
THE LEGEND OF THE FROSTY TEMPLE?

04:35.441 --> 04:37.568
both: OOH, TELL US! TELL US!

04:37.652 --> 04:39.195
- LEGEND HAS IT THE FROSTY MART

04:39.278 --> 04:42.240
WAS BUILT UPON THE TOMB
OF AN ANCIENT KING,

04:42.323 --> 04:45.618
AND RUINS OF HIS TEMPLE,
AND ITS CURSE,

04:45.702 --> 04:48.454
WERE BURIED
BY THE SANDS OF TIME,

04:48.538 --> 04:52.333
BENEATH THIS VERY ROOM.

04:52.417 --> 04:53.751
both: [gasp]

04:53.835 --> 04:56.129
- REALLY?

04:56.212 --> 04:57.547
- BEATS ME.

04:57.630 --> 04:59.590
WHY DON'T YOU SPEND
A FEW DAYS IN HERE AND FIND OUT?

04:59.674 --> 05:02.135
both: YAY!

05:02.218 --> 05:04.470
[hammering]

05:04.554 --> 05:05.930
- [laughs manically]

05:06.014 --> 05:07.390
FROSTY AIRWAYS?

05:07.473 --> 05:08.891
I NEED A PLANE TO PICK ME UP
AT THE FROSTY MART RIGHT AWAY.

05:08.975 --> 05:11.227
[garbled phone chatter]

05:11.310 --> 05:13.104
I DON'T CARE
IF YOU DON'T HAVE ANY PLANES.

05:13.187 --> 05:17.066
I'M A VACATION WINNER!
SEND AIR FROST ONE!

05:17.150 --> 05:19.777
I'M GETTING ON THAT PLANE
IF IT'S THE LAST THING I DO.

05:19.861 --> 05:21.446
[growls]

05:23.281 --> 05:26.159
- WOW, SO THIS IS WHERE
THEY KEEP THE DARKNESS.

05:26.242 --> 05:30.747
- OOH, OOH! TAKE MY PICTURE
NEXT TO THE DARKNESS.

05:30.830 --> 05:31.497
[shutter snaps]

05:31.581 --> 05:36.335
- HEY, WHAT'S THAT DOOR?

05:36.419 --> 05:38.588
- HELLO-O?

05:38.671 --> 05:42.800
DREAM VACATION WINNERS HERE.

05:42.884 --> 05:44.093
[door creaks open]

05:44.177 --> 05:45.762
both: OOH.

05:45.845 --> 05:47.597
[magical music]

05:47.680 --> 05:56.272
WHOA, THE ANCIENT TEMPLE.

05:56.355 --> 05:57.398
[gasp]

05:57.482 --> 06:00.443
[mysterious instrumental music]

06:00.526 --> 06:07.742
♪ ♪

06:07.825 --> 06:10.119
- OOH.

06:10.203 --> 06:12.038
OOH. OOH.

06:12.121 --> 06:14.373
IT'S NICE AND TOMB-Y.

06:14.457 --> 06:15.875
WHAT'S WRITTEN ON THE WALLS?

06:15.958 --> 06:18.086
- SOME KIND OF LANGUAGE.

06:18.169 --> 06:19.754
IT'S VERY DIFFICULT TO READ.

06:19.837 --> 06:21.047
- ENGLISH?

06:21.130 --> 06:21.964
- COULD BE.
HARD TO KNOW.

06:22.048 --> 06:24.884
OH, PERFECT.

06:24.967 --> 06:29.472
{\an5}[recorded female voice]
WELCOME TO THE AUDIO TOUR
OF THE TOMB OF KING BOY.

06:29.555 --> 06:34.811
MANY YEARS AGO,
THERE LIVED A YOUNG BOY KING--

06:34.894 --> 06:36.312
KING BOY.

06:36.395 --> 06:40.441
HE WAS TALL AND HANDSOME
AND NOT THE LEAST BIT ANNOYING.

06:40.525 --> 06:43.277
- BOY, THEY HAD
SOME FLAT HEADS BACK THEN.

06:43.361 --> 06:45.154
- [recorded voice]
IN THOSE DAYS,

06:45.238 --> 06:48.407
THERE LIVED A MERCHANT
NAMED LENSES.

06:48.491 --> 06:53.037
HE WAS KNOWN ACROSS THE LAND
FOR HIS GRUMPY TEMPERAMENT

06:53.121 --> 06:55.790
AND TERRIBLE CUSTOMER SERVICE.

06:55.873 --> 06:59.502
- HERE'S YOUR STUPID--
I MEAN, OH, ROYAL KING BOY,

06:59.585 --> 07:03.464
HERE IS THE BEVERAGE
YOU REQUESTED.

07:03.548 --> 07:06.467
- OOH, A SANDY, SALTY SLURP.

07:06.551 --> 07:07.468
[slurps]

07:07.552 --> 07:09.512
[belches]

07:09.595 --> 07:13.850
OH, LENSES,
WILL YOU PULL MY FINGER?

07:13.933 --> 07:14.642
- NO.

07:14.725 --> 07:16.352
- HOW ABOUT NOW?
- NO!

07:16.435 --> 07:17.395
- HOW ABOUT NOW?

07:17.478 --> 07:18.354
- LEAVE ME ALONE!

07:18.437 --> 07:19.939
- LENSES, I AM YOUR KING.

07:20.022 --> 07:21.899
- [growls]

07:21.983 --> 07:22.900
[flies buzzing]

07:22.984 --> 07:25.236
- [laughing]

07:25.319 --> 07:27.321
- I LIKE THAT KING.
HE'S FUNNY.

07:27.405 --> 07:28.698
- [laughing]

07:28.781 --> 07:30.366
- [recorded voice]
LENSES GREW TIRED

07:30.449 --> 07:37.039
OF THE KING'S HILARIOUS ANTICS,
AND HE HATCHED AN EVIL PLAN.

07:37.123 --> 07:40.710
PLEASE PRESS 12 IF YOU WISH
TO HEAR LENSES' EVIL PLAN.

07:40.793 --> 07:46.007
SO LENSES LOCKED KING BOY
IN A PYRAMID.

07:46.090 --> 07:48.885
LENSES GLOATED
ABOUT HIS CLEVERNESS,

07:48.968 --> 07:51.387
BUT HIS ACTIONS DID NOT SIT WELL

07:51.470 --> 07:55.183
WITH THE ANCIENT GOD,
CHUMNUBIS.

07:55.266 --> 07:58.561
CHUMNUBIS CAST
A POWERFUL CURSE ON LENSES

07:58.644 --> 08:00.605
THAT TURNED HIM TO DUST

08:00.688 --> 08:03.316
SO THAT HE WOULD
BE A NUISANCE TO ALL

08:03.399 --> 08:05.651
FOR THE REST OF ETERNITY.

08:05.735 --> 08:08.112
WE HOPE YOU'VE ENJOYED
THIS AUDIO TOUR

08:08.196 --> 08:09.405
OF THE TOMB OF KING BOY.

08:09.488 --> 08:11.949
PLEASE STOP BY OUR GIFT SHOP
AS YOU EXIT THE TOMB.

08:12.033 --> 08:14.285
both: GIFT SHOP!

08:14.368 --> 08:16.037
[giggling]

08:16.120 --> 08:18.414
- [impatiently]
AHH, COME ON.

08:18.497 --> 08:19.916
WHEN'S THAT PLANE
GOING TO GET HERE?

08:19.999 --> 08:21.292
- both: LENNY! LENNY! LENNY!

08:21.375 --> 08:23.419
LENNY! LENNY! LENNY!

08:23.502 --> 08:24.754
- YOU WERE RIGHT!

08:24.837 --> 08:28.382
THAT LOST TEMPLE IS AMAZING.

08:28.466 --> 08:29.717
- LOST TEMPLE?

08:29.800 --> 08:32.094
THE ONLY THING LOST AROUND HERE
IS YOUR MARBLES.

08:32.178 --> 08:34.847
[snaps]
UH-UH-UH.

08:34.931 --> 08:36.015
- THAT'S FUNNY.

08:36.097 --> 08:37.933
I ALMOST BOUGHT MARBLES
AT THE GIFT SHOP.

08:38.017 --> 08:38.601
INSTEAD, I GOT THIS:

08:38.683 --> 08:41.895
THE STAFF OF CHUMNUBIS.

08:41.979 --> 08:44.732
DUN-DUN!

08:44.815 --> 08:48.152
- COME ON, CHUM CHUM,
LET'S BLAST THIS CURSED THING.

08:48.236 --> 08:49.237
TEE-HEE-HEE-HEE-HEE!

08:49.320 --> 08:51.113
- GIFT SHOP?

08:51.197 --> 08:53.115
- "CONGRATULATIONS
ON YOUR PURCHASE

08:53.199 --> 08:54.617
"OF A STAFF OF CHUMNUBIS.

08:54.700 --> 08:57.495
"YOU CAN LOOK FORWARD
TO MANY FUN HOURS

08:57.578 --> 08:59.664
OF CURSING FRIEND
AND FOE ALIKE."

08:59.747 --> 09:01.749
- OOH, I'M LENSES.

09:01.832 --> 09:05.461
- AND NOW I JUST NEED
TO SELECT YOUR CURSE.

09:05.544 --> 09:08.589
HOW ABOUT POX OF OSIRIS?

09:08.673 --> 09:09.674
[laser shoots]

09:09.757 --> 09:11.968
- AH! WHAT?
WHAT'S HAPPENING?

09:12.051 --> 09:13.970
- AM I POXED?
AM I POXED?

09:14.053 --> 09:15.763
- HMM.
DOESN'T LOOK LIKE IT.

09:15.846 --> 09:18.557
LET'S TRY RAMSES' LAMENT.

09:18.641 --> 09:21.394
- OOH, I WONDER WHAT THAT DOES.

09:21.477 --> 09:22.645
[laser shoots]

09:22.728 --> 09:24.563
- AHH!

09:24.647 --> 09:28.567
AH, MY HAIR! MY GORGEOUS HAIR!

09:28.651 --> 09:31.487
- [disappointedly]
AW, THAT ONE WAS A DUD.

09:31.570 --> 09:33.948
- LET'S GO FOR
MOUTHFUL OF STEAKS.

09:34.031 --> 09:34.824
- MOUTHFUL OF STEAKS?

09:34.907 --> 09:38.286
THAT DOESN'T SOUND SO BAD.

09:38.369 --> 09:40.496
- WAIT!
STOP!

09:40.579 --> 09:41.539
PUT THAT THING DOWN!

09:41.622 --> 09:43.082
[laser shoots]

09:43.165 --> 09:44.458
[screams]

09:44.542 --> 09:48.004
- OH, IT SAYS SNAKES,
NOT STEAKS.

09:48.087 --> 09:50.756
- YEAH, NO SNAKE MOUTH HERE.

09:50.840 --> 09:52.174
- STOP!

09:52.258 --> 09:59.932
[hissing] PUT THAT SINISTER
SCEPTER BACK IN THE STOREROOM!

10:00.016 --> 10:02.059
IT'S AIR FROST ONE!

10:02.143 --> 10:05.021
THEY'RE NOT GOING TO STOP ME.

10:05.104 --> 10:08.024
- OOH, SEARING SANDS
OF THE SAHARA.

10:08.107 --> 10:09.191
OOH, THAT SOUNDS EXOTIC.

10:09.275 --> 10:10.276
[laser shoots]

10:10.359 --> 10:11.652
- [screams]

10:11.736 --> 10:13.362
AH! OOH, AH! AH!

10:13.446 --> 10:14.363
AH! OOH! AH!

10:14.447 --> 10:16.532
- SCORCHING WINDS OF THE DESERT.

10:16.615 --> 10:17.533
[laser shoots]

10:17.616 --> 10:19.118
- AH! PTOO! PTOO!

10:19.201 --> 10:21.620
- PLAGUE OF THE SCARABS.

10:21.704 --> 10:22.038
[laser shoots]

10:22.121 --> 10:24.040
- AH!

10:24.123 --> 10:24.540
[beetles scuttling]

10:24.623 --> 10:26.208
[whimpering]

10:26.292 --> 10:28.377
[screams]

10:28.461 --> 10:31.422
AH! AH! BEETLES! AH!

10:31.505 --> 10:33.007
- FALLING PIANO OF ROCK?

10:33.090 --> 10:33.632
- [whimpers]

10:33.716 --> 10:34.967
[soaring whistle]

10:35.051 --> 10:36.010
UH-OH.

10:36.093 --> 10:38.637
[muffled scream]

10:38.721 --> 10:41.390
- THAT'S FUNNY; I DIDN'T THINK
THEY HAD PIANOS BACK THEN.

10:41.474 --> 10:43.559
- ALL RIGHT, WELL,
HERE'S THE LAST ONE:

10:43.642 --> 10:46.354
THE FULL MUMMY.

10:48.481 --> 10:49.190
- [groaning]

10:49.273 --> 10:51.567
- TICKETS, PLEASE.

10:51.650 --> 10:53.277
- [hissing]
CERTAINLY.

10:53.361 --> 10:54.195
HERE YOU GO.

10:54.278 --> 10:55.404
[laser shoots]

10:55.488 --> 10:56.405
WAH?

10:56.489 --> 10:59.075
[screaming]

10:59.158 --> 11:01.994
[muffled groaning]

11:04.872 --> 11:06.916
- TAKE CARE NOW.
BUH-BYE.

11:06.999 --> 11:11.087
- WELL, CHUM CHUM, THIS THING
JUST DIDN'T WORK AS ADVERTISED.

11:11.170 --> 11:14.632
- CHEAP SOUVENIR STORE GARBAGE.

11:14.715 --> 11:17.635
- OH, HELLO, YOUNG BOYS.

11:17.718 --> 11:21.514
WE'VE GOT TWO EMPTY SEATS
ON A PLANE TO PARADISE.

11:21.597 --> 11:25.768
CAN I INTEREST YOU IN A FREE
FROSTENTATIOUS ADVENTURE?

11:25.851 --> 11:26.268
- ANOTHER VACATION?

11:26.352 --> 11:27.645
I COULD USE IT.

11:27.728 --> 11:31.065
- YEAH,
THAT LAST VACATION TIRED ME OUT.

11:32.733 --> 11:35.444
BOY, LENNY REALLY SHOULD
SWEEP THIS PARKING LOT.

11:35.528 --> 11:38.155
IT'S REALLY DUSTY.

11:39.698 --> 11:43.619
- COULD SOMEBODY BLOW ME
TO THE BEACH?

11:47.039 --> 11:48.958
[maniacal laughter]

11:49.041 --> 11:51.961
[sinister music]

11:52.044 --> 11:54.922
♪ ♪

11:57.550 --> 11:59.885
- both: FIELD TRIP!

11:59.969 --> 12:01.595
all:
WE'RE GOING ON A FIELD TRIP!

12:01.679 --> 12:03.514
WE'RE GOING ON A FIELD TRIP.

12:03.597 --> 12:05.474
- WOULD YOU KINDLY
STOP BOUNCING?

12:05.558 --> 12:08.144
I'M NOT ACCUSTOMED
TO SINGLE-DECKER BUSES,

12:08.227 --> 12:10.521
AND MY STOMACH IS QUITE...

12:10.604 --> 12:12.314
[gags]
SENSITIVE.

12:12.398 --> 12:14.692
- OH, BOY, A FIELD TRIP.

12:14.775 --> 12:16.277
THIS IS SO EXCITING.

12:16.360 --> 12:19.321
I BET THERE'S FIELDS
AS FAR AS THE EYE CAN SEE.

12:19.405 --> 12:21.240
- OOH, I HOPE THERE'S RAGWEED
AND GOPHER HOLES.

12:21.323 --> 12:23.659
[door slams]

12:23.742 --> 12:26.078
- IF THIS BUS KEEPS A-ROCKIN'...

12:26.162 --> 12:28.289
I'M COMING A-KNOCKIN'!

12:28.372 --> 12:29.331
all: [gasp]

12:29.415 --> 12:31.750
LUNCH LADY CRAM.

12:31.834 --> 12:34.753
- LUNCH LADY CRAM'S MY SISTER.

12:34.837 --> 12:37.423
I'M BUS LADY CRAM.

12:37.506 --> 12:39.925
- OH, YEAH, YOU BOTH HAVE
THE SAME PRETTY SNARL.

12:40.009 --> 12:42.178
- [growls]

12:42.261 --> 12:44.180
- UH, BUS LADY CRAM?

12:44.263 --> 12:47.099
SHOULDN'T WE
BE GOING TO THE FIELD?

12:47.183 --> 12:49.351
WOULDN'T WANT
TO MISS THE MOSQUITOES.

12:49.435 --> 12:53.022
- WE'RE NOT GOING TO ANY FIELD!

12:53.105 --> 12:57.485
MY SISTER SAYS
THE CAFETERIA'S OUT OF FOOD,

12:57.568 --> 12:59.695
SO WE'RE GOING TO...

12:59.778 --> 13:02.615
THE GLOP MINES.

13:02.698 --> 13:04.366
all: GLOP MINES?

13:04.450 --> 13:06.994
[screaming]

13:07.077 --> 13:08.871
- I'M OUT OF HERE, MAN!

13:11.624 --> 13:12.541
[whimpers]

13:12.625 --> 13:18.297
[windows slamming shut]

13:18.380 --> 13:20.257
- OH, DEAR,
WE'RE TRAPPED ON THE BUS,

13:20.341 --> 13:21.926
AND WE'RE HEADING
FOR THE GLOP MINES.

13:22.009 --> 13:24.011
SUDDENLY, I DON'T FEEL SO...

13:24.094 --> 13:25.429
[coughing and splattering]

13:25.513 --> 13:27.431
- THIS IS SUPPOSED
TO BE A FIELD TRIP, ISN'T IT?

13:27.515 --> 13:29.850
WELL, START SINGING!

13:32.186 --> 13:35.314
all: ♪ 99 BUCKETS
OF GLOP ON THE WALL ♪

13:35.397 --> 13:37.066
♪ 99 BUCKS OF GLOP ♪

13:37.149 --> 13:40.444
- [laughs manically]

13:40.528 --> 13:42.571
[engine revving]

13:42.655 --> 13:45.699
[screaming]

13:49.328 --> 13:50.913
[wind whistling]

13:50.996 --> 13:52.456
- [growls]

13:52.540 --> 13:55.084
- THE GLOP MINES?

13:55.167 --> 13:59.380
YOU MEAN, WE'RE GOING TO SEE
WHERE CAFETERIA FOOD COMES FROM?

13:59.463 --> 14:00.422
I DON'T WANT TO SEE.

14:00.506 --> 14:02.550
I DON'T WANT TO SEE!

14:02.633 --> 14:04.510
- SHH, IT'S OKAY, CHUM CHUM.

14:04.593 --> 14:06.262
I'LL POKE YOUR EYES OUT.

14:06.345 --> 14:08.180
- PROMISE?

14:08.264 --> 14:09.598
- QUIET BACK THERE!

14:09.682 --> 14:11.350
- YOU KNOW WHAT I HEARD?

14:11.433 --> 14:12.768
THAT WHEN A BUS
GOES TO THE GLOP MINES,

14:12.851 --> 14:15.312
IT NEVER COMES BACK TO SCHOOL.

14:15.396 --> 14:17.106
- EVER?

14:17.189 --> 14:19.066
BUT I LEFT MY CHALK BACK THERE.

14:19.149 --> 14:22.236
[dramatic music]

14:22.319 --> 14:23.153
[whimpers fearfully]

14:23.237 --> 14:24.905
- NO, YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.

14:24.989 --> 14:27.825
THEY SAY THERE'S
A MONSTER IN THE MINES,

14:27.908 --> 14:33.455
AND IT EATS THE CHILDRENS
DOWN TO THEY BONES.

14:33.539 --> 14:34.790
all: [gasp]

14:34.873 --> 14:36.875
- OH, WAIT,
IT JUST EATS CHILDREN?

14:36.959 --> 14:39.211
[chuckling]
OH, THANK GOSH.

14:39.295 --> 14:43.716
- OH, I'M SURE
THIS ALL A BUNCH OF POPPYCOCK

14:43.799 --> 14:45.968
INVENTED TO SCARE US CHILDREN.

14:46.051 --> 14:48.679
- [unseen voice]
NO, IT'S TRUE.

14:48.762 --> 14:49.972
- [gasps]
WHO SAID THAT?

14:50.055 --> 14:55.978
- I DID, FOR I ALONE
SURVIVED TO TELL THE...

14:56.061 --> 14:57.438
- A DIRTY KID!

14:57.521 --> 14:58.689
all: [gasps]

14:58.772 --> 15:00.608
- OH, HE LOOKS HUNGRY.

15:00.691 --> 15:02.985
QUICK, GIVE HIM SOME FOOD
FROM YOUR LUNCHES.

15:03.068 --> 15:05.779
- OH, BLESS YOU, SIR.
BLESS YOU.

15:05.863 --> 15:06.822
I'VE BEEN LIVING OFF
PORRIDGE I MAKE

15:06.905 --> 15:09.992
FROM SEAT STUFFING
AND PENCIL STUBS.

15:10.075 --> 15:11.076
- HERE, MY HAM SANDWICH.

15:11.160 --> 15:13.829
- EH, DON'T LIKE HAM.
GOT BOLOGNA?

15:13.912 --> 15:14.788
- I'M SAVING IT.

15:14.872 --> 15:15.873
- TRADE YOU MY CRISPS?

15:15.956 --> 15:16.832
- NO WAY.

15:16.915 --> 15:17.833
- TOSS IN A PUDDING?

15:17.916 --> 15:18.375
- DEAL. NO BACKSIES.

15:18.459 --> 15:20.461
- [chomping]

15:20.544 --> 15:23.505
[belches loudly]

15:23.589 --> 15:25.507
OH, THAT'S BETTER.

15:25.591 --> 15:26.550
NOW, WHERE WAS I?

15:26.634 --> 15:28.761
- THE GLOP MONSTER?

15:28.844 --> 15:30.888
- OH, RIGHT, RIGHT.

15:30.971 --> 15:32.181
HE'S A BEAST!

15:32.264 --> 15:35.017
THE BLACKEST TERROR!

15:35.100 --> 15:39.980
FIRST, HE GRABS YOU
AND SPINS YOU 'ROUND.

15:40.064 --> 15:42.733
- [whimpering]
OH, NO.

15:42.816 --> 15:46.695
- THEN IT SWALLOWS YOU
IN ITS GAPING MOUTH.

15:46.779 --> 15:51.367
- AYE, I CAN'T LISTEN.

15:51.450 --> 15:54.078
- YOU TRAVEL THROUGH
ITS PITCH-BLACK GULLET,

15:54.161 --> 15:56.413
TORTURED BY THE SCREAMS
OF YOUR COMPANIONS.

15:56.497 --> 15:58.749
- [gulps]

15:58.832 --> 16:00.709
- AND JUST WHEN YOU THINK
IT'S DON WITH YOU,

16:00.793 --> 16:03.128
IT SPITS YOU OUT!

16:03.212 --> 16:03.545
- [glugging]

16:03.629 --> 16:05.172
PTOO.

16:05.255 --> 16:06.548
- AND THEN IT SUCKS YOU BACK IN!

16:06.632 --> 16:09.009
- [inhales sharply]

16:09.093 --> 16:12.763
- WHY, ME AND TIMMY
WERE THE ONLY ONES WHO GOT OUT.

16:12.846 --> 16:13.389
ISN'T THAT RIGHT, TIMMY?

16:13.472 --> 16:14.431
[bone snaps]

16:14.515 --> 16:16.725
all: [screams]

16:16.809 --> 16:20.270
- HEY, NO PANICKING!

16:20.354 --> 16:23.982
AND TELL THAT SKELETON
TO PUT ON A SEAT BELT.

16:24.066 --> 16:24.900
- [frantically]
WE'VE GOT TO GET OFF THIS BUS.

16:24.983 --> 16:27.569
- THERE'S NO GETTING OFF
THE BUS.

16:27.653 --> 16:29.238
YOU'RE DOOMED!

16:29.321 --> 16:32.574
DOOMED, I TELL THEE!

16:32.658 --> 16:35.577
ANYONE WANT TO SWAP A LEMONADE
FOR A FRUIT PUNCH?

16:35.661 --> 16:37.579
- WHY DIDN'T I
THINK OF IT BEFORE?

16:37.663 --> 16:40.416
I CAN USE MY WAND TO SAVE US.

16:40.499 --> 16:43.168
- KYLE, YOU CAN DO MAGIC?

16:43.252 --> 16:44.294
- [groans]

16:44.378 --> 16:45.754
STAND BACK.

16:45.838 --> 16:51.301
I WILL NOW TRANSPORT US BACK TO
THE SCHOOL FROM WHENCE WE CAME.

16:51.385 --> 16:55.305
REVERSE US, FIELD TRIPPER CURSE!

16:55.389 --> 17:00.310
OH, HEH, IT LOOKS LIKE
SHE DIDN'T SHUT EVERY WINDOW.

17:01.770 --> 17:04.565
- OH, COULD'VE USED THAT STICK
FOR STIRRING ME PORRIDGE.

17:04.647 --> 17:05.648
THAT'S TOO BAD.

17:05.733 --> 17:08.109
all: [whining]

17:08.193 --> 17:10.279
- FIVE MILES TO THE GLOP MINES,
FANBOY.

17:10.362 --> 17:11.113
WHAT ARE WE GOING TO DO?

17:11.195 --> 17:13.741
- [chattering and whimpering]

17:13.824 --> 17:15.867
DOLLAR-NATOR.
HE CAN HELP US.

17:15.951 --> 17:17.161
I JUST NEED TO USE
MY TRUSTY WRIST COMMUNICATOR.

17:17.243 --> 17:20.705
BOOP, BOO-DO-DO-BOOP, BOOP.
COME IN, DOLLAR-NATOR.

17:20.789 --> 17:23.040
- [grunting]

17:23.125 --> 17:23.459
FEEL THE BURN.

17:23.541 --> 17:25.335
WORK IT.

17:25.419 --> 17:27.212
[beeping]

17:27.296 --> 17:27.628
YOU'VE GOT DOLLAR-NATOR.

17:27.713 --> 17:29.840
[sips]

17:29.923 --> 17:32.301
- DOLLAR-NATOR, WE'RE ON THE
ROAD TRIP TO THE GLOP MINES.

17:32.384 --> 17:33.427
WE NEED YOUR HELP.

17:33.510 --> 17:35.345
- LET ME TRIANGULATE
YOUR LOCATION.

17:35.429 --> 17:36.805
I'M PULLING YOU UP
ON GOOGLE MAPS.

17:36.889 --> 17:41.477
OOH, ARE YOU AWARE YOU ARE ONLY
0.75 MILES FROM YOGURT WORLD?

17:41.560 --> 17:43.520
WOULD YOU LIKE ME
TO CLICK ON THIS COUPON?

17:43.604 --> 17:45.230
- LATER.

17:45.314 --> 17:46.315
RIGHT NOW, WE NEED TO KNOW HOW
TO STOP A YELLOW SCHOOL BUS.

17:46.398 --> 17:49.318
- OKAY,
I'VE GOT THE BUS-SCINATICS.

17:49.401 --> 17:52.362
THERE'S A MASTER CONTROL PANEL
AT THE FRONT OF BUS.

17:52.446 --> 17:53.530
GO NOW,
I'LL GUIDE YOU THROUGH IT.

17:53.614 --> 17:56.825
GO, GO, GO!

17:56.909 --> 17:59.286
- WE'VE GOT TO BE
AS STEALTH AS POSSIBLE.

17:59.369 --> 18:02.456
- [growling]

18:02.539 --> 18:03.123
[gasps]

18:03.207 --> 18:06.126
A KITTY IN THE ROAD!

18:06.210 --> 18:06.543
[tires screeching]

18:06.627 --> 18:07.544
- AHH!

18:07.628 --> 18:09.379
THWACK!

18:12.716 --> 18:14.802
- OOPS, JUST AN ARMADILLO...

18:16.553 --> 18:17.513
[loud bump]

18:17.596 --> 18:18.472
AND HIS FAMILY.

18:18.555 --> 18:20.766
[loud bumps]

18:20.849 --> 18:21.642
HEY!

18:21.725 --> 18:23.519
WHAT DO YOU THINK YOU'RE DOING?

18:23.602 --> 18:26.355
- UM, UH, OH, UH,
I JUST THOUGHT--

18:26.438 --> 18:29.775
OH, YOUR FEET MUST BE SO TIRED
FROM ALL THAT DRIVING.

18:29.858 --> 18:31.401
YOU'D PROBABLY ENJOY
A FOOT MASSAGE.

18:31.485 --> 18:33.821
EH? EH?

18:33.904 --> 18:37.032
- I LOST ALL FEELING IN MY FEET
YEARS AGO,

18:37.115 --> 18:40.035
BUT YOU CAN GO TO WORK
ON THOSE CORNS.

18:40.118 --> 18:43.121
- ECHH.

18:43.205 --> 18:44.122
[gasps]

18:44.206 --> 18:46.041
[dramatic music]

18:46.125 --> 18:46.583
[fly buzzing]

18:46.667 --> 18:50.087
[gagging]

18:50.170 --> 18:52.214
WOULD YOU HURRY UP, FANBOY?

18:52.297 --> 18:53.549
SHE'S GOT TRENCH FOOT.

18:53.632 --> 18:55.008
I DON'T KNOW HOW LONG
I CAN HOLD OUT!

18:55.092 --> 18:57.427
- JUST BREATHE
THROUGH YOUR MOUTH.

18:57.511 --> 18:58.887
I'M ON IT!

18:58.971 --> 19:00.222
[suspenseful music]

19:00.305 --> 19:03.684
I'M AT THE PANEL.
WHAT NOW?

19:03.767 --> 19:05.894
- NOW YOU SHOULD SEE SOME WIRES.

19:05.978 --> 19:07.145
- UH-HUH.

19:07.229 --> 19:08.564
- IT'S VERY SIMPLE.

19:08.647 --> 19:11.483
ALL YOU HAVE TO DO
IS CUT THE BLACK WIRE.

19:11.567 --> 19:12.651
GOT IT?

19:12.734 --> 19:14.153
- CUT THE BLACK WIRE?
GOT IT.

19:14.236 --> 19:17.406
OKAY, I DON'T SEE A BLACK WIRE,
BUT I DO SEE A DARK GREEN ONE,

19:17.489 --> 19:21.618
A BROWN ONE--OOH, THIS ONE
HAS BLACK DIAMONDS ON IT.

19:21.702 --> 19:25.372
- HEY, WHAT ARE YOU DOING
IN MY SNAKE TANK?

19:25.455 --> 19:26.331
- HUH?

19:26.415 --> 19:27.291
[snake hisses]

19:27.374 --> 19:28.834
- I KEEP 'EM NEXT TO MY WIRES.

19:28.917 --> 19:31.795
- AHH!
SNAKES ON A BUS!

19:31.879 --> 19:33.630
- JUST FOR THAT LITTLE STUNT,

19:33.714 --> 19:38.260
I'M DRIVING TO THE GLOP MINES
EVEN FASTER.

19:38.343 --> 19:39.595
- [grunts]

19:39.678 --> 19:43.891
I WAS BREATHING THROUGH THERE.
FANBOY, DO SOMETHING!

19:43.974 --> 19:45.142
- [nervously]
I AM.

19:45.225 --> 19:47.811
I'M TRYING NOT TO MOVE.

19:47.895 --> 19:49.021
[snakes hissing]

19:49.104 --> 19:50.522
[screeching]

19:50.606 --> 19:51.857
- AH!

19:51.940 --> 19:53.525
BETTY! SANCHO!

19:53.609 --> 19:54.943
MAMA'S DRIVIN'.

19:55.027 --> 19:57.738
- NOT ANYMORE.
HA HA!

19:57.821 --> 19:59.406
[tires screeching]

19:59.489 --> 20:01.950
- [Dollar-nator over radio]
FANBOY, COME IN.

20:02.034 --> 20:04.161
WHY DID YOU DIVERT YOUR COURSE?

20:04.244 --> 20:06.496
- I HAD TO GET US
AWAY FROM THE GLOP MINES.

20:06.580 --> 20:09.958
- YEAH, BUT YOU'RE HEADING FOR
THE WORLD'S LARGEST SPEED BUMP.

20:10.042 --> 20:10.959
- EH?

20:11.043 --> 20:11.960
- [shrieks]

20:12.044 --> 20:14.379
[engine revving]

20:14.463 --> 20:17.633
all: [screaming]

20:17.716 --> 20:20.636
[percussive music intensifying]

20:20.719 --> 20:23.805
[music dwindling]

20:23.889 --> 20:27.476
- [chattering and whimpering]

20:27.559 --> 20:29.978
WE'RE...WE'RE IN SPACE.

20:30.062 --> 20:31.313
WHEE!

20:31.396 --> 20:33.941
- WHOA.

20:34.024 --> 20:37.444
- WHOO-HOO, NOW THIS
IS WHAT I CALL A FIELD TRIP.

20:37.527 --> 20:39.988
- OH, WOULD YOU LOOK AT THAT?

20:40.072 --> 20:44.743
THE EARTH ROTATED JUST ENOUGH
TO BRING OUR TRAJECTORY

20:44.826 --> 20:48.497
ON A DIRECT COURSE
RIGHT FOR THE GLOP MINES.

20:48.580 --> 20:49.831
[laughs]

20:49.915 --> 20:52.668
[engine revving]

20:52.751 --> 20:56.838
[children screaming]

20:56.922 --> 21:01.259
- [laughing manically]

21:05.263 --> 21:06.848
[engine smoking]

21:06.932 --> 21:10.894
[children groaning]

21:10.978 --> 21:11.937
- OH...

21:12.020 --> 21:15.482
OH, NO, LOOK WHERE WE ARE!

21:15.565 --> 21:17.192
[dramatic music]

21:17.275 --> 21:18.902
[glop glugging]

21:18.986 --> 21:21.780
- IT'S THE GLOP MINES.

21:21.863 --> 21:25.200
- AND THERE'S THE GLOP MONSTER.

21:25.283 --> 21:28.245
[monster exhaling]

21:28.328 --> 21:29.496
- [shrieks]

21:29.579 --> 21:32.624
HE'S GOING TO GRAB US
AND SPIN US AROUND

21:32.708 --> 21:35.544
AND THEN SWALLOW US
IN ITS FIERY MOUTH!

21:35.627 --> 21:38.380
- WE'RE GOING TO TRAVEL
THROUGH ITS PITCH-BLACK GULLET,

21:38.463 --> 21:40.507
TORTURED BY THE SCREAMS
OF OUR COMPANIONS.

21:40.590 --> 21:43.218
- AND JUST WHEN WE THINK
IT'S DONE WITH US,

21:43.301 --> 21:46.763
IT'S GOING TO SPIT US OUT
THEN SUCK US BACK IN.

21:46.847 --> 21:47.723
[crying]

21:47.806 --> 21:51.435
[ominous music]

21:51.518 --> 21:53.603
- OF COURSE THAT'S WHAT HE DOES,

21:53.687 --> 21:57.607
'CAUSE IT'S THE MOST WICKED
ROLLERCOASTER YOU'VE EVER SEEN.

21:57.691 --> 21:59.860
[children cheering]

21:59.943 --> 22:02.362
- THAT'S THE GLOP MONSTER?

22:02.446 --> 22:03.697
- SURE IS.

22:03.780 --> 22:04.614
WELL, WHAT ARE YOU WAITING FOR?

22:04.698 --> 22:05.991
[sneers]

22:06.074 --> 22:08.785
[windows slam open]

22:08.869 --> 22:11.413
[carnival music]

22:11.496 --> 22:13.081
- NOW YOU CAN SEE WHY
THE BUS NEVER CAME BACK.

22:13.165 --> 22:15.959
EVERYONE WAS HAVING SO MUCH FUN.

22:16.043 --> 22:18.754
I JUST LEFT
BECAUSE I HAD TUBA PRACTICE.

22:18.837 --> 22:21.214
- BUT--BUT WHAT ABOUT TIMMY?

22:21.298 --> 22:22.841
- I WON HIM AT RING TOSS.

22:22.924 --> 22:25.552
IT WAS THIS
OR THE STUFFED PANDA.

22:25.635 --> 22:27.971
- SO THERE'S NOT REALLY
A VICIOUS GLOP MONSTER

22:28.055 --> 22:29.014
THAT EATS CHILDREN?

22:29.097 --> 22:30.891
- [laughs]
THAT'S RIDICULOUS.

22:30.974 --> 22:34.686
IT ONLY EATS TEACHERS.

22:34.770 --> 22:36.438
- [frantically]
IT EATS WHAT NOW?

22:36.521 --> 22:38.774
[gurgling]

22:38.857 --> 22:40.609
[monster chomping]

22:40.692 --> 22:44.613
WHY DOES THIS HAPPEN
EVERY FIELD TRIP?

22:47.407 --> 22:50.285
Captioning by CaptionMax
www.captionmax.com

22:50.368 --> 22:51.328
[melodic whistling]

22:51.411 --> 22:53.038
- WHOA!

22:53.121 --> 22:56.124
[quirky electronic music]

22:56.208 --> 23:00.045
♪ ♪

23:00.128 --> 23:03.131
[melodic whistling]

23:03.215 --> 23:11.223
♪ ♪
